node.text:
For #WorldRefugeeDay today, I’m delighted to hand over my Instagram account to Nhial Deng. He has an incredibly powerful story to share. Check out my Stories later today, to hear it in his own words… 
 
Throughout Nhial’s continued and tireless community activism, his message is simple: all refugees deserve to rebuild and contribute to society - even more so in the time of COVID-19. Follow him on @nhial_gabe - and @refugees for more inspiring voices. Thank you! #WithRefugees

node.title: World Refugee Day - meet Nhial Deng!

Her message ahead of #WorldRefugeeDay is one we all need to hear. Every action counts. Please watch and find out how you can support @refugees by clicking the link in my bio. #COVID19 #WithRefugees

node.text:
This woman is my inspiration.

#WorldRefugeeDay is coming, and I reunited over Zoom with the incredible Nida who puts her life and soul into her work helping @refugees. When we met Syrian families in Jordan, she helped me understand their stories and their futures. But even she could not have imagined the impact of #COVID19.  Like Nida, so many UNHCR workers are staying and delivering on the ground, continuing to help those in need. Everyone can help make a difference. Every action counts. Please watch and click the link in my bio to find out more.

#RefugeeDay #WithRefugees

node.title: Meeting UNHCR's Nida Yassin - World Refugee Day

node.text:
Lots more Sandman Act II casting in this little video. Act II will drop on September the 22nd. And a lot of you are going to be able to listen to Act I for free between now and October 22nd. If you haven't heard it, you can listen to it for free, with no strings attached, before Act II comes out. (The rules on how you can listen to it and whether it's free may change depending on where you are in the world. For now, The Sandman is available free for all listeners in the US with no strings attached, and for Audible members in Australia. And there’s more to come.) 

Sandman Act II takes us through the entirety of Season of Mists and A Game of You, with some of the short stories on the way. It will be about the same length as Act I.

(And the Sandman Act II cast is obviously huger than this video -- Justin Vivian Bond is back as Desire, Aiden Turner is Cluracan, Sian Philips is Livia, Ray Porter and Kerry Shale return as, well, everyone... and this doesn't even get into the cast of A Game of You.)

For #WorldRefugeeDay today, I’m delighted to hand over my Instagram account to Nhial Deng. He has an incredibly powerful story to share. Check out my Stories later today, to hear it in his own words… 
 
Throughout Nhial’s continued and tireless community activism, his message is simple: all refugees deserve to rebuild and contribute to society - even more so in the time of COVID-19. Follow him on @nhial_gabe - and @refugees for more inspiring voices. Thank you! #WithRefugees

node.text: I stayed in Auckland for a couple of days after the Writers Festival, to try and get on top of a few deadlines. This is the view from my hotel room window.  It's back to the island and my family this afternoon. I love the cheerful little Whatever in the photo. The possibilities are endless.

node.text: Such a wonderful documentary! I got an out of the blue call from Edgar Wright. "You like Sparks, don't you?" he asked, although we had never talked about them. I admitted I did. That was how he got us all to talk. The Sparks Brothers is Edgar Wright's documentary about Sparks, the band. It's a delight. Out in the US in June, in the UK in July...

node.text: Ash was sent a big box of TRICKS by his friend Tennyson, back in America. The kind you used to see advertised in the back of comics, a long time ago. A Joy buzzer, a Floating Eyeball and the rest of them. When I was a small boy I used to dream of obtaining some and wreaking chaos on an unsuspecting world. (Although I believed that the life-sized submarine you could buy for a dollar was actually a submarine. And that sea monkeys smoked pipes and wore pearls under water.) Anyway, I am delighting in his joy...
